ChatGPT said:

It seems like your C++ code has a few errors and improvements that can be made. Below is a corrected version:

  1. Include necessary headers: You need to include the <vector> and <algorithm> headers to use vector and sort.
  2. Correct the condition in the loop: The loop condition has an error (for(int i=1; i*i<=n; i++) instead of for(int i=1; i<i*i<=n; i++)).
  3. Correct the modulus operation: Instead of n/i==0, it should be n % i == 0.
  4. Use != for inequality: Replace !== with !=.

Here’s the corrected code:

cpp
#include<iostream>
#include<vector>
#include<algorithm>
using namespace std;

void print(int n) {
    vector<int> li;
    for(int i = 1; i * i <= n; i++) {
        if(n % i == 0) {
            li.push_back(i);
            if(n / i != i) {
                li.push_back(n / i);
            }
        }
    }
    sort(li.begin(), li.end());
    for(auto it : li) cout << it << " ";
}

int main() {
    int n;
    cout << "Enter the number: ";
    cin >> n;
    print(n);
    return 0;
}

Explanation:

  • Headers: <vector> is included for std::vector, and <algorithm> is included for std::sort.
  • Condition: The loop iterates up to sqrt(n), checking for divisors.
  • Push Divisors: If i is a divisor, both i and n/i are added to the list, unless they are the same.
  • Sorting and Printing: The divisors are sorted and then printed.

This program will print all divisors of the entered number in sorted order.
